speech.p: On Friday, the BBC interviewed an Egyptian economic migrant in Calais who said that he had tried and failed four times to cross the channel but, since the Prime Ministers agreement with President Macron, he was giving up:
I dont want to go to Britain any more, because they are making it much harder for us. Every time we try, they deflate our boats and remove the engine. If they make it even harder, Ill stop trying.
Does that not prove that this new deal to send migrants back to France can be a genuine deterrent, unlike the last Governments pathetic attempt to claim credit?
